<h1 id='linux-basic'>Linux Basic</h1><h2 id='shortcut-keys'>Shortcut keys</h2>
<ul>
<li><code>ctrl + alt + T</code> - Open terminal</li>
<li><code>ctrl + alt + &lt;up/right/left&gt;</code> - Switch workspace</li>
<li><code>ctrl + alt + shift + &lt;right/left&gt;</code> - Move current window right/left workspace</li>
<li><code>ctrl + alt + &lt;F1/F2/F3/F4/F5/F6&gt;</code> - Open TTY login (does not use GUI)</li>
<li><code>ctrl + alt + &lt;F7&gt;</code> -  Leave TTY screen and switch to GUI</li>
</ul>
<h2 id='basic-commands'>Basic commands</h2>
<ul>
<li><code>man &lt;cmd&gt;</code> - list manual pages for any valid linux <code>cmd</code></li>
<li><code>pwd</code> - path of working directory</li>
<li><code>cd folder</code> - changes the current directory to <code>folder</code></li>
<li><code>cd ..</code> - change the directory to one level up except at &#39;/&#39;</li>
<li><code>cd -</code>   jumps to previous <code>pwd</code> before a <code>cd</code></li>
<li><code>ls -l</code> - long listing the file</li>
<li><code>ls -lrt</code> - list file based on the modified date. recent at the last.</li>
</ul>
<pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code><span class="gp">$ </span>ls            <span class="c"># list the contents of current directory</span>
<span class="gp">$ </span>cat file.txt  <span class="c"># list the contents of file.txt if exist</span>
</code></pre>